          "course_name": "Mathematics",
          "curriculum_blurb": "",
          "comment": "It is a pleasure to work with Kelsey again this year.  She continues to be a strong math student and a pleasure to have in class.  Kelsey is a bright girl with an inherent number sense, strong reasoning skills, and good conceptual understanding.  Kelsey can also be a big picture thinker who sees patterns and easily consolidates new ideas with her existing knowledge to propel her understanding further.\n\nKelsey is creative when working orally, both in group discussions and one on one.  She approaches mathematical problems with logical and well-thought-out solutions.  Her peers benefit from her astute explanations, and she exhibits obvious pride in being able to share her thoughts successfully.\n\nKelsey is still less sure of herself when tasks involve a lot of reading.   In these instances, Kelsey sometimes skips over the words and tries to figure out what she should do based on the numbers she sees on the page; this strategy often works but sometimes leads to errors on her assignments, despite her obvious understanding of the material and mastery of the skills involved.  At other times, Kelsey can be daunted when faced with long written directions and simply disengage from the task at hand.  She loses heart when this type of assignment takes her longer than she wants, and I have seen a drop in both her enthusiasm and her confidence in math class lately.  I endeavor to impress upon Kelsey my appreciation of her strengths as a math student, and I hope to see her self-assurance grow as her reading skills continue to develop.  \nHilary Harris, 1/7/19",
