          "comment": "Maxx is a bright, kind, and energetic boy who is a pleasure to have in class. Maxx is a well-liked member of our group and enjoys contributing to class discussions. Maxx is easily distracted by interactions with his peers, and he benefits from many teacher reminders to maintain attention throughout the class. Maxx thrives from a predictable schedule, consistent routine, and a structured environment in his small language group.\n \nMaxx is reading on grade level with excellent comprehension. When focused, he can retell a story with great detail and can make nice connections to the characters in each book he reads. When asked to write in response to a text independently, Maxx is less sure of himself and benefits from clear expectations before he can begin. Maxx is working to organize the words on each page while writing. He benefits from extra space and broader lines on his paper as well as reminders to use neat handwriting and use ample space between words as he writes.\n \nMaxx needs to continue to bring his home book bag to and from school, as he needs new books. \n \nAcademic goals for Maxx that we are supporting:\n\nContinued support in planning and organizing writing responses\nIndependently expanding his writing responses without being required to write a specific number of sentences\nChecking over his work before handing it in\nBuilding his stamina and confidence in writing\nUsing finger spaces between each word while writing\nImproving his reading fluency\nSpelling accuracy on his weekly dictations and in his independent work\nStaying on task during class discussions and lessons\nBringing his book bag to and from school as he needs new books",
