          "comment": "Fox can be internally motivated to produce high caliber work. At times he devotes his full energies and focus to whatever project is in front of him. He is also able to block out the noise around him in a busy classroom and devote his creative mind to producing the best work of which he is capable.  \n\nFox is able to comfortably take risks, assert himself when necessary, and enjoy sharing his accomplishments. Fox can also follow both oral and written directions, and he is able to accept suggestions from teachers.\n\nFox often requires direct one-to-one teacher support to keep him on track and focused on the work in front of him. If he finds the work at all tedious, he is then unable to sit independently and complete the task. \n\nWhere we also continue to support Fox is in his notable fidgeting during meetings and work time.  Fox knows there is always a stool available to him that has a convex base, allowing movement during sitting activities. Fox frequently asks for and uses the stool, and it has proven to be a useful outlet for his energy.",
