          "curriculum_blurb": "",
          "comment": "Max is a passionate and endearing young boy who brings with him a determination and impressive intensity to all he approaches. Max is good friends with Isaac and Alex and the three share a love of sports that they often discuss with animation. Max greets his teachers in the morning with a cheery hello and is excited to share stories, particularly about baseball. For example, he regaled us with tales of the struggles of the Astros and was extremely pleased when a teacher was able to share in his conversation. \n\nMax continues to work on expanding his social network of friends in 2A. On occasion,  Max has become impatient when paired with a student with whom he usually does not interact. When this happens he benefits from a teacher quietly modeling for him how to use more encouraging words. Max is also a naturally competitive young boy, and we support him in working on focusing on the quality of his own work without first comparing himself to others.\n\nMax’s parents have shared with us that at home he expresses great sadness and unhappiness about school. But while at school, Max’s affect is most often one of happiness, excitement, and even joy. We will continue to monitor the discrepancy between what he tells his parents about school and the lighthearted young boy we enjoy in class.",
