          "comment": "Isaac is a highly engaging, bright, and effervescent part of our classroom community.  Every morning Isaac greets his teachers with a reserved smile, but beams at his many friends in 2A. Children are naturally drawn to Isaac’s fair-minded and compassionate nature. \n\nDuring out time, Isaac loves throwing a baseball around with children such as Alex and Max, with whom he’s particularly close. The three are often gathered together in the classroom as well, talking about baseball or playing a rousing card game.  \n\nIsaac exudes tremendous positive energy and enjoys sharing ideas and observations with both children and adults.  At times, he is bursting at the seams with something he wishes to share and needs to be reminded to refrain from talking to a friend during a lesson. But once reminded, he most often looks contrite and quickly reengages once again. \n\nWe also sometimes need to remind Isaac to respond to his name the first time it is called. When Isaac is laughing and playing with friends it may take a few times of calling his name before he acknowledges the teacher.",
